# Case 03 — BEC & Credential Harvesting: Splunk Log Investigation

Case ID: DFIR-2024-003  
Classification: High  
Investigator: Himanshu Chourasia  
Tools: Splunk SPL, Chainsaw, Sigma Rules, Hayabusa, Magnet AXIOM  
Duration: 6 hours (detection → full scope → containment)

---

## Executive Summary

A Business Email Compromise (BEC) attack targeting a manufacturing company's CFO resulted in an attempted fraudulent wire transfer of €420,000. The threat actor phished a Finance Manager, harvested Office 365 credentials via an adversary-in-the-middle (AiTM) proxy, bypassed MFA, and used inbox rules to hide correspondence from the victim. Splunk log analysis across Azure AD, O365 audit logs, and endpoint telemetry revealed the full attack chain within 6 hours — in time to freeze the outgoing transfer.

