## Investigation Walkthrough

### Phase 1 — Splunk: Initial Detection & Scoping

#### Impossible Travel Detection

The initial alert was triggered by a custom Splunk correlation search detecting logins from geographically impossible locations within a short time window.

```spl
index=azure_ad sourcetype=azure:aad:signin
| eval login_time=strptime(CreatedDateTime, "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")
| sort user, login_time
| streamstats current=f last(login_time) as prev_time last(IPAddress) as prev_ip by user
| eval time_diff_mins=round((login_time - prev_time)/60, 2)
| iplocation IPAddress
| iplocation prefix=prev_ prev_ip
| eval speed_kmh=if(isnotnull(lat) AND isnotnull(prev_lat),
    round(geodistance(lat, lon, prev_lat, prev_lon) / (time_diff_mins/60), 0), null())
| where speed_kmh > 900 AND time_diff_mins < 30
| table user, IPAddress, Country, prev_ip, prev_Country, time_diff_mins, speed_kmh
```

Output:
```
user         IPAddress        Country      prev_ip         prev_Country  time_diff  speed_kmh
-----------  ---------------  -----------  --------------  ------------  ---------  ---------
rmehra       185.220.101.12   Netherlands  49.36.201.44    India         3.8 min    14,271
```

