### Phase 2 — Inbox Rule Forensics

#### Enumerating Malicious Inbox Rules

```spl
index=o365_audit Operation="New-InboxRule" OR Operation="Set-InboxRule"
| spath input=Parameters
| eval rule_name=mvindex(Parameters{}.Value, 0)
| eval conditions=mvindex(Parameters{}.Value, 1)
| table _time, user, IPAddress, Operation, rule_name, conditions
```

Malicious rule detected:
```
Time:       2024-03-13 11:34:07 UTC
User:       rmehra
Operation:  New-InboxRule
Rule Name:  "AutoArchive_FIN"
Conditions: SubjectContainsWords: [invoice, payment, wire, transfer, urgent, approval]
Actions:    MoveToFolder: Deleted Items, MarkAsRead: True
```

> The inbox rule silently moved and marked-as-read all finance-related emails — preventing the victim from seeing the fraudulent correspondence being sent in their name.

