### Phase 4 — Chainsaw: Windows Event Log Corroboration

Chainsaw was run against the endpoint logs from `rmehra`'s workstation to confirm no persistence was established locally.

```bash
chainsaw hunt D:\Cases\DFIR-2024-003\EventLogs\ \
  --sigma sigma_rules/ \
  --mapping mappings/sigma-event-logs-all.yml \
  --output chainsaw_results.csv \
  --level medium
```

Key findings from Chainsaw:
```
[HIGH]   Suspicious PowerShell Download Cradle               — NOT FOUND
[HIGH]   Scheduled Task Creation via Schtasks                — NOT FOUND  
[MEDIUM] O365 Login from New Country                         — FOUND (Netherlands)
[MEDIUM] Multiple Failed MFA Attempts Before Success         — FOUND (3 failures, 1 success)
[LOW]    OWA Access Outside Business Hours                   — NOT APPLICABLE (11:33 UTC = business hours)
```

> The 3 failed MFA attempts before success is consistent with AiTM attack behaviour — the proxy relays credentials and session tokens in real time, sometimes requiring a few attempts as the victim completes MFA.

